 :tx/rationale "Create task: SOUND-ISO-v2: Incremental/Batch Duality Invariant — INV-STORE-IDX-005. CONTEXT: The original SOUND-ISO tested only MaterializedViews.fitness() vs compute_fitness(). But this is ONE instance of a GENERAL pattern. The Store has FOUR incremental data structures that can diverge from their batch-recomputed equivalents: (1) MaterializedViews.fitness() vs compute_fitness_batch(), (2) live_view[(e,a)] vs resolve(ConflictSet::from_datoms(e,a)), (3) entity_index[e] vs rebuild_entity_index_from_datoms(), (4) frontier[agent] vs Frontier::from_datoms(). Each pair can diverge independently. Testing them one at a time catches only one bug class at a time. THE FORMAL FIX is a new spec invariant: INV-STORE-IDX-005: 'Every incrementally-maintained data structure in the Store MUST have a batch-recompute function, and for any store state S: incremental(S) == batch(S). Falsification: any sequence of transactions that causes incremental(S) \\!= batch(S) for any of the four pairs.' APPROACH: (1) Create spec element INV-STORE-IDX-005 via braid spec create. (2) Create batch-recompute functions that already exist or are trivial to add: (a) compute_fitness_batch is compute_fitness() in bilateral.rs, (b) resolve_live_value_batch scans all datoms for (e,a) and applies LWW — this is what from_datoms does inline, (c) rebuild_entity_index iterates all datoms grouping by entity — this IS from_datoms logic extracted, (d) Frontier::current already computes from datoms. (3) Create proptest test_incremental_batch_duality: (a) Strategy: generate random sequence of 20-50 transactions with mixed Assert/Retract ops, varying entities, attributes, values. (b) After applying all txns via transact(), verify all 4 equalities. (c) Also verify after merge() of two independently-built stores. (4) Create unit test test_isomorphism_with_retractions: Build store with spec elements, impl links, tasks, observations, retracted datoms, multi-cardinality attrs. Compare all 4 pairs component-by-component. (5) For MaterializedViews specifically: compare each of 7 F(S) components independently (validation, coverage, drift, contradiction, incompleteness, uncertainty, harvest_quality). KNOWN DIVERGENCE PATHS: (a) observe_datom ignores Retract (line 612) — counters are monotonic. (b) impl/verification-depth is a no-op in observe_datom (lines 634-643). (c) task_open/task_in_progress/task_closed never decrement (lines 690-706). If the proptest FINDS a divergence, that is itself a P0 finding requiring immediate fix. ACCEPTANCE: (A) INV-STORE-IDX-005 spec element created. (B) Proptest passes for random 50-transaction sequences OR documents specific known divergences. (C) Each of the 4 incremental/batch pairs is tested. (D) For F(S): all 7 components compared independently. (E) Test covers stores built via transact() AND merge(). (F) Known divergences documented with TODO tasks. FILE: crates/braid-kernel/src/store.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/bilateral.rs, crates/braid-kernel/src/proptest_strategies.rs. TRACES-TO: INV-STORE-IDX-005 (new), INV-BILATERAL-001, INV-STORE-012. BLOCKS: nothing directly, but finding divergence would re-prioritize Phase A."
